SIMPLE: wash_out
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wash out
<hw>Wash out</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i. & t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>to be removed by washing; -- of spots and stains, especially on
clothing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>to be removed, broken, or destroyed by the action of
flowing water; <as>as, the bridge was <ex>washed out</ex> by the
flood</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>to fail in a course of study or training, especially
to leave before completion of the course.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Washpot</ent>⟦br⟧
